{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect RB tree comparison function in M3AP association management\n\n### Summary\nThe M3AP association management code contained a flawed comparison function for the Red-Black trees used to store MME/MCE association data. The `m3ap_MME_compare_assoc_id` and `m3ap_MCE_compare_assoc_id` functions had special-case logic that would incorrectly compare by `cnx_id` when `assoc_id` was -1, causing search operations to fail.\n\nThis bug manifested when trying to look up M3AP associations by their SCTP association ID, particularly during handover procedures where the system would fail to find existing associations and attempt to create duplicate entries.\n\nThe issue was introduced when the code was adapted from X2AP/S1AP implementations but the RB tree ordering logic was not properly adjusted for M3AP's usage patterns.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/M3AP/m3ap_MME_management_procedures.c`: Simplified `m3ap_MME_compare_assoc_id` to always compare by `assoc_id`\n- `openair3/M3AP/m3ap_MCE_management_procedures.c`: Applied same fix to `m3ap_MCE_compare_assoc_id`\n\n"
}